    "X_cal": ["X", "X_train"],
    "X_val": ["X_test", "X_validation"]
  },
  "short_description": "Centers and/or normalizes spectroscopic data",
  "long_description": "Preprocessing step that centers and/or normalizes data to improve model performance. Essential preparation for multivariate calibration methods.\n\nCentering:\n- Subtracts column means from all samples\n- Removes baseline/offset effects\n- Centers data around zero\n- Recommended for most applications\n\nNormalization (Autoscaling):\n- Divides by column standard deviations\n- Scales each variable to unit variance\n- Gives equal weight to all variables\n- Important when variables have different scales/units\n- Particularly useful for spectroscopic data\n\nCombination Effects:\n\nCentering Only:\n- Removes offset differences between samples\n- Preserves variance structure\n- Good when variables are on same scale\n\nNormalization Only (rare):\n- Without centering, less common\n- Useful for specific data distributions\n\nBoth Centering + Normalization (recommended):\n- Standard preprocessing for chemometrics\n- Equal treatment of all variables\n- Improves model stability and interpretability\n- Required for most PLS and PCR applications\n\nMultiway Data:\n- Works with 2D, 3D, and higher dimensional data\n- Direction parameter specifies axis\n- Default direction (-1) applies along last axis\n\nNote: Validation data will be transformed using calibration statistics during modeling.",
  "setup": {
    "categories": ["Processing Options", "Data Inputs", "Multiway Configuration"],
    "layout": [
      {
        "name": "center",
        "label": "Center Data",
        "category": "Processing Options",
        "widget": "checkbutton",
        "default": true,
        "required": true,
        "input_type": "user",
        "tooltip": "Subtract column means (centering/mean-centering)"
      },
      {
        "name": "normalize",
        "label": "Normalize Data",
        "category": "Processing Options",
        "widget": "checkbutton",
        "default": false,
        "required": true,
        "input_type": "user",
        "tooltip": "Scale to unit variance (autoscaling)"
      },
      {
        "name": "direction",
        "label": "Direction (for multiway, -1=default)",
        "category": "Multiway Configuration",
        "widget": "entry",
        "type": "int",
        "default": "-1",
        "required": false,
        "input_type": "user",
        "tooltip": "Dimension along which to center/normalize (-1 for default)"
      },
      {
        "name": "X_cal",
        "label": "X Calibration Data",
        "category": "Data Inputs",
        "widget": "data_input",
        "required": true,
        "input_type": "routed",
        "visible_if": {"input_type": "user"},
        "tooltip": "Routed from previous function output"
      },
      {
        "name": "X_val",
        "label": "X Validation Data",
        "category": "Data Inputs",
        "widget": "data_input",
        "required": false,
